# 1\. Formal Definitions (Textbook Section)

### Dual-Column Format: IGSOA ↔ Standard Mathematics

| IGSOA / MBC-4.0 Formalism | Standard Mathematics Interpretation |
| :---- | :---- |
| μ-field \= local semantic weight density | Scalar weight function μ(x) ≥ 0 unless marked negative |
| Micro-Adjacency Grid \= stable local neighborhood relation of a Box or Tensor-Node | Fixed graph adjacency list; no topological mutation allowed |
| μ-adjacency pair (i,j) | Weighted edge eᵢⱼ with weight μᵢⱼ |
| μ-tensor \= weight-indexed domain tensor | Weighted incidence matrix |
| μ-Jacobian / μ-Laplacian | Weighted divergence-form operators |
| Invariant preservation under δ, Φ, Π, ψ, λ flows | Operators cannot break positivity or adjacency structure |

# 2\. Weighted / Adjacency Invariants (μ-Family)

### Invariant 1 — Local Weight Positivity Invariant

Any μ-weight must satisfy:  
μ ≥ 0 unless explicitly annotated μ± for signed weight.  
Formal form:  
μi∈R≥0unlessflag(i)="signed"

### Invariant 2 — Micro-Adjacency Conservation

The μ-adjacency grid cannot spontaneously change its topology.  
No operator may create or destroy adjacency relations.  
Formal form:  
Adjt+1=Adjtunless an explicit REWIRE event is declared.

---

### Invariant 3 — Weighted-Adjacency Compatibility

For any adjacency pair (i,j):  
If (i,j) ∈ Adj, then μᵢⱼ must exist and be finite.  
---

### Invariant 4 — Weighted-Flow Stability under δ-Deformation

δ-curvature cannot force μ negative or cause adjacency splitting.  
---

### Invariant 5 — μ-Commutativity with Φ and Π

Φ(μ-structure) preserves classes,Π(μ) preserves evaluation ordering.  
Φ(μ-structure) preserves classes,Π(μ) preserves evaluation ordering.

## 2\. Tier-04 → Tier-05 Curvature Bridge

Now we connect μ / adjacency (Tier-04) to λ / curvature (Tier-05).

### 2.1 Dual-Column Conceptual Bridge

| IGSOA / MBC-4.0 | Standard Geometry / Analysis |
| :---- | :---- |
| μ-field on adjacency grid | Weight function on a graph / manifold |
| λᶜᵘʳᵛ acting on μ | Curvature-induced deformation of a weight field |
| λ respects A1–A3 | Curvature cannot create negative densities or break topology |
| μ-Jacobian, μ-Laplacian | Weighted gradient/divergence/Laplacian |
| λ-μ flow equation | Curvature flow PDE with invariant-preserving constraints |
| NF\_μAdj \+ λ-theorem | Weighted graph remains well-posed under curvature evolution |

We want:  
Any λ-operation on a Tier-04 μ-Adj state must result in another μ-Adj invariant-safe state, i.e. NF\_μAdj is stable under λ.
